{"lemma":"دِينِ","slug":"دِينِ","root":"د.#.ن","root_slug":"د-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/د-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دِين","root":"دين","pos":"N","occurrence_count":92},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26469","n13587","n13586","n13590"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَانَ (dāna, “to be religious”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"religion, creed, credo, faith, conviction, belief, tenet, rite","tags":["countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"لَكُمْ دِينُكُمْ وَلِيَ دِينِ","english":"For you is your religion, and for me is my religion."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conformism, conformance, conformity, compliance, fealty, obedience; God-fearingness, godliness, religiosity, devoutness","tags":["noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"law, obligations, duty"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"custom, habit","examples":[{"text":"لَيْسَ هٰذَا مِنْ دِينِي وَلَا دَيْدَنِي","english":"This is not according to my habit nor to my wont."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"judgement, decision, ruling; requital, compensation, indemnification","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"judgement, decision, ruling; credit, obligation, account, falling due of a debt","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"religious, pious, godly, God-fearing, devout"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to religiousize"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to loan, to lend, to advance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَانَ (dāna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"debt, debit, liability, pecuniary, obligation, financial claim"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"A historically conflated term derived from multiple layers of phono-semantic matching:\n* Initially stemming from Proto-Semitic *dVn- (“obligated conduct; decisions of morality or ethics, judgement, decree, ruling”), where in Arabia it took specifically the foremost connotation of obligations, duty, what is expected or owed; hence also the sense of a monetary debt along with that which is owed to society ethically.\n* Cognate terms in other Semitic languages also came with a more developed legal sense, rulings, a set of obligations, a law code; these senses were bolstered semantically borrowing from Aramaic דִּינָא (dīnā), Classical Syriac ܕܺܝܢܳܐ (dīnā, “judgement”), Hebrew דִּין (din), Ge'ez ደይን (däyn, “judgement”), which likely had their specified development from Akkadian 𒁲 (dīnum, “judgement; legal practice, precedent; legal case; court conduct, procedures, rule of law”). Another possible layer still is Sumerian 𒁲 (di /⁠did⁠/, “lawsuit, trial; legal decision”) which is a term of uncertain origins; potentially an early Akkadian borrowing, at least semantically, or natively derived from 𒁲 (di, “to speak”), a form of 𒅗 (dug₄ /⁠dug⁠/, “to speak, talk, say; to order, to negotiate”).\n* The sense of religious creed or a system of religious rules is borrowed from Middle Persian [Book Pahlavi needed] (dyn' /⁠dēn⁠/), which developed from Old Persian *dainah (“a religious-informed or conscientious way of life”). Developing also from Younger Avestan 𐬛𐬉𐬥𐬁 (dēnā), a term already having a predecessor with a religious sense in Avestan 𐬛𐬀𐬉𐬥𐬁 (daēnā), which is possibly akin to Sanskrit ध्यान (dhyāna), whence zen. This possibly derives in part under the influence of Elamite, developing from the Akkadian legal sense; religious obligation to deities, the system or conduct of the priesthood regarding divinities.\n* The Qurʾān and later Islamic scholarship adds an additional layer of phono-semantic matching, melding the native significations with the connotations imparted by the languages of their neighbors, both from the Semitic family and those not.\n\nFrom the verb دَانَ (dāna, “to hold religion”).\n\nCausative of the verb دَانَ (dāna, “to be a debtor”).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/diːn/","/daj.ja.na/","/dajn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26469","headword_ar":"دِينٌ","root":"Tdw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) the latter word formed by transposition from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waATidN","text_ar":"وَاطِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdapN","text_ar":"عَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAdiyapN","text_ar":"طَادِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) the latter word said to be formed by transposition from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waATidapN","text_ar":"وَاطِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A custom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit, that is constant, settled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"established; old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inveterate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAdK","text_ar":"طَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waATidN","text_ar":"وَاطِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are also expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Continuous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constant and uninterrupted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wTd","text_ar":"وطد"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n13587","headword_ar":"دِينٌ","root":"dyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is an inf. n. of 1: and is also used as a simple subst., signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Obedience;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynapN","text_ar":"دِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K: [in the M it is said, without any restriction, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynapN","text_ar":"دِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynN","text_ar":"دِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) this is its primary meaning: and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoyaAnN","text_ar":"اَدْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, as some say, its primary meaning is that next following: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of abasement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissiveness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~iynu lil~`hi","text_ar":"الدِّينُ لِلّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Obedience to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the service of, God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K. *) And the saying, in the Kur [iv. 124],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa mano A^aHosanu","text_ar":"وَ مَنْ اَحْسَنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynFA mimano A^asolama wajohahu lil~`hi","text_ar":"دِينًا مِمَنْ اَسْلَمَ وَجْهَهُ لِلّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And who is better"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in obedience"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than he who resigns himself to God?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Er-Rághib, TA.) In like manner, also, in the same [ii. 257],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A_ikoraAha fiY Ald~iyni","text_ar":"لَا اـِكْرَاهَ فِى الدِّينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no compulsion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in obedience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, and in one of my copies of the S:) pl. as above: (S:) so termed as implying obedience, and submission to the law: [for ex.,] it is said in the Kur [iii. 17],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Ald~iyna Einoda A@ll~`hi A@loA_isolaAmu","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الدِّينَ عِنْدَ ا@للّٰهِ ا@لْاـِسْلَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the"},{"kind":"text","text":"only true"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religion in the sight of God is El-Islám"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~iynu","text_ar":"الدِّينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That whereby one serves God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K.) [It is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Religion, in the widest sense of this term, practical and doctrinal:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus comprehending"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iymaAnu","text_ar":"الاـِيمَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means “ religious belief. ”] And it [particularly] signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The religion of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-Islám."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The religious law of God; consisting of such ordinances as those of fasting and prayer and pilgrimage and the giving of the poor-rate, and the other acts of piety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of obedience to God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of duty to Him and to men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ariyEapu","text_ar":"الشَّرِيعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The belief in the unity of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Piety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pious fear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstinence from unlawful things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaraEu","text_ar":"الوَرَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A particular law; a statute;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ordinance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, and Jel in xii. 76) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDaA='N","text_ar":"قَضَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Katádeh, T, K.) It is said in the Kur [xii. 76],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kaAna liyaA^oxu*a A^axaAhu fiY","text_ar":"مَا كَانَ لِيَاْخُذَ اَخَاهُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diyni A@lomaliki","text_ar":"دِينِ ا@لْمَلِكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Joseph)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was not to take his brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a slave for the theft"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to the law of the king"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Egypt; i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Hukomi","text_ar":"فِى حُكْمِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maliki miSora","text_ar":"مَلِكِ مِصْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Jel,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fYqaDaAy^ihi","text_ar":"فىقَضَايِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Katádeh, T;) for his punishment according to him was beating, and a fine of twice the value of the thing stolen; not enslavement: (Jel:) or, accord. to ElUmawee, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the dominion of the King."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A system of usages,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rites and ceremonies"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inherited from a series of ancestors."},{"kind":"text","text":"] It is said in a trad., of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna EalaY diyni qawomihi","text_ar":"كَانَ عَلَى دِينِ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He used to conform with the old usages obtaining among his people, inherited from Abraham and Ishmael, in respect of their pilgrimage and their marriagecustoms"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and their inheritances"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and their modes of buying and selling and their ways of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and other ordinances of the faith"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]; (IAth, TA;) but as to the belief in the unity of God, they had altered it; and the Prophet held no other belief than it: (IAth, K, TA:) or, as some say, the meaning here is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their dispositions, in respect of generosity and courage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynN","text_ar":"دِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense next following. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Custom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, T, S, M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynapN","text_ar":"دِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"business:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) pl., as above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoyaAnN","text_ar":"اَدْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) This, also, has been said to be the primary signification. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zaAla","text_ar":"مَا زَالَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika diyniY","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ دِينِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That has not ceased to be my custom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadobiyrN","text_ar":"تَدْبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Management, conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regulation, of affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"State, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) ISh says, I asked an Arab of the desert respecting a thing, and he said to me,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo laqiytaniY EalaY dinK gayori h`*ihi laA^axobarotuka","text_ar":"لَوْ لَقِيتَنِى عَلَى دِنٍ غَيْرِ هٰذِهِ لَاَخْبَرْتُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hadst thou found me in a state other than this, I had informed thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A property, such as is an unknown cause of a known effect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAS~iy~apN","text_ar":"خَاصِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (KL. [The significations of “ Via ” and “ Signum ” and “ Opera, ” mentioned by Golius as from the KL, I do not find in my copy of that work.])       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Disobedience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [Thus it bears a signification the contr. of that first mentioned in this paragraph.]       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Repayment, requital, compensation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) or, as some say, such as is proportioned to the deed of him who is its object. (TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAliki yawomi Ald~iyni","text_ar":"مَالِكِ يَوْمِ الدِّينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The King"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the day of requital,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur [i. 3]: (M, T, TA:) or the meaning in this instance is the next but one of those here following. (T, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Retaliation, by slaying for slaying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wounding for wounding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mutilating for mutilating."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A reckoning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K.) [See the sentence next but one above.] Hence, in the Kur [ix. 36],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~iynu Alqay~imu","text_ar":"الدِّينُ القَيِّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is said to mean]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is the right, correct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true, reckoning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Compulsion against the will:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subdual, subjection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subjugation; ascendency: sovereign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruling, power;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power of dominion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mastership,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ownership;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exercise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possession, of authority."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A disease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, IAar, T, S, M, K:) or, accord. to El-Mufaddal,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old disease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T.)       -A6-  [It is said to signify also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A constant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gentle, rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynapN","text_ar":"دِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) accord. to the book of Lth, [by which is meant the 'Eyn,] (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain that has been constantly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usually,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recurring in a place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:) but this is a mistake of Lth, or of some one who has added it in his book: a verse of Et- Tirimmáh, there cited as an ex., ends with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadiyni","text_ar":"وَدِينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is in that instance syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoduwn","text_ar":"مَوْدُون"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “ moistened; ” its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the primal radical, not the conjunction"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynN","text_ar":"دِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning any kind of rain being unknown. (T, TA.)       -A7-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^inN","text_ar":"دَايِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","M","K","S","Joseph","Jel","IAth","T","Lh","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n13586","headword_ar":"دَيْنٌ","root":"dyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is an inf. n. of 1: ―         -b2-  and is also a simple subst., and] properly signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A debt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"price of a thing sold"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the purchaser is under an obligation to pay"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dowry"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which one engages to pay"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a loan,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroD","text_ar":"قَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or it is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a debt"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as has an appointed time of falling due:"},{"kind":"text","text":"what"},{"kind":"page_break","n":944},{"kind":"text","text":"has not such an appointed time is [properly, but not always,] termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroDN","text_ar":"قَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynapN","text_ar":"دِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayonN","text_ar":"دَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K) in the sense above explained: (K:) a valid"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayno","text_ar":"دَينْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daynN SaHiyHN","text_ar":"دَينٌ صَحِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as does not become annulled save by payment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by one's being declared clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"compensation in the case of a contract which a slave makes with his owner to pay him a certain sum as the price of himself and on the payment thereof to be free is not a valid"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayon","text_ar":"دَيْن"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it may become annulled without payment, and without his being declared clear, or quit; that is, by the slave's being unable to pay it: (KT:) in the language of the law, but not in the proper language,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayonN","text_ar":"دَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a debt incurred by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing taken unjustly, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by violence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayon","text_ar":"دَيْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly so called: (Msb:) and it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is not present:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything to be paid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"done, at a future time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M, K:) the pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoyunN","text_ar":"اَدْيُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duyuwnN","text_ar":"دُيُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) [and in the CK is added and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynapN","text_ar":"دِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr; but this is a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dinotuhu","text_ar":"دِنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adanotuhu","text_ar":"اَدَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which follows it, connected therewith by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynapN","text_ar":"دِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diyanN","text_ar":"دِيَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^akovra dayonahu","text_ar":"مَا اَكْثرَ دَيْنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynatahu","text_ar":"دِينَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How great in amount. is his debt!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; both meaning the same. (AZ, T.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otu liTalabi Ald~iynapi","text_ar":"جِيْتُ لِطَلَبِ الدِّينَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ayoni","text_ar":"الدَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came for the demanding of the debt"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AZ, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi dayonN","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ دَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On him lies a debt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he owes a debt"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu dayonN","text_ar":"لَهُ دَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To him is due a debt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has a debt owed to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otaraY","text_ar":"اِشْتَرَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAld~ayoni","text_ar":"بِالدَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bought upon credit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a Ald~ayona","text_ar":"اَخَذَ الدَّيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKt, M, Msb, K) or [rather]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a","text_ar":"اَخَذَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayonFA","text_ar":"دَيْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifies the same; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, upon credit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, a loan,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like; he borrowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a bidayonK","text_ar":"اَخَذَ بِدَيْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise signifies the same; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, by incurring a debt"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEa","text_ar":"بَاعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAld~ayoni","text_ar":"بِالدَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sold upon credit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEovuhu","text_ar":"بِعْثُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidayonK","text_ar":"بِدَيْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidiynapK","text_ar":"بِدِينَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sold to him upon credit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTayotuhu Ald~ayona","text_ar":"اَعْطَيْتُهُ الدَّيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifies the same; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"granted him, credit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"granted him, the loan,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) because it is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayon","text_ar":"دَيْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or debt] which every one must pay when [the angel who is] the demander of its payment comes. (TA.) And hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAhu A@ll~`hu bidayonihi","text_ar":"رَمَاهُ ا@للّٰهُ بِدَيْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God smite him with his death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  Thaalebeh Ibn-'Obeyd says, describing palm-trees,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"taDam~anu AlHaAjaAti AlEiyaAli wa Dayofihimo\n                      \n                     \n                        wamahomaA taDam~ano mino duyuwnihimo taqoDi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They comprise the wants of the household and of their guest; and whatever they comprise of their debts, they pay"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duyuwn","text_ar":"دُيُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning what is obtained of their fruit that is gathered. (M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","T","M","KT","Lh","S","IKt","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13590","headword_ar":"دَيِّنٌ","root":"dyn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Religious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who makes himself a servant of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaday~inN","text_ar":"مُتَدَيِّنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}